page.title: 09St Annes - Local News.
page.content: {The following was culled from local {newspaper Lytham St Annes Express} {price}17pence. June 6: Volunteers help conserve sand- dunes. Dunes will be stabilised with sand-trap fencing and marram grass. Most erosion caused by people walking through dunes,people will be asked to keep to paths.The 18th World Veterans Road Running Championships took place at weekend.Age ranges 35-89 from all corners of globe.Newly-opened Plaza Bingo club had over 2,000 weekly visitors.Working-class families in area could be hit by Government plans reviewing welfare state,older couples, no families might benefit.Seasonal work caused drop in unemployed.1,593 compared with 1,654 the previous month.Tory party regaining dominance in South Fylde politics following county elections.
